public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) {
            return false;
        }
        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }
        return n == 1;
    }
}
```

This solution works by continuously dividing the input number by 3 until it is no longer divisible by 3. If the final result is 1, then the original number was a power of three. If the final result is not 1, then the original number was not a power of three.

Here is a more mathematical solution that uses logarithms:

```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) {
            return false;
        }
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
